 in 1845 and in 1885|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Engels|first=Friedrich|year=2004|title=Collected Works|volume=50|location=New York|publisher=International Publishers|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Esping-Andersen|first=G\u00f8sta|year=1985|title=Politics Against Markets: The Social Democratic Road to Power|publisher=Princeton University Press|isbn=9780691654188|jstor=j.ctt1m322zp|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Feuchtwanger|first=Edgar|year=2002|title=Bismarck|publisher=Routledge|isbn=9780415216142|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Fitzpatrick|first=Tony|year=2003|title=After the New Social Democracy: Social Welfare for the Twenty-First Century|publisher=Manchester University Press|isbn=9780719064777|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Foley|first=Michael|year=1994|title=Ideas that Shape Politics|publisher=Manchester University Press|page=23|isbn=978-0-7190-3825-9|quote=The virtual demise of communism [as represented by the Soviet Union and other communist states] has opened up the way for democratic socialism or social democracy as the major alternative to ''laissez-faire'', free market policies.|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last1=Franks|first1=Peter|last2=McAloon|first2=Jim|title=Labour: The New Zealand Labour Party 1916\u20132016|year=2016|publisher=Victoria University Press|location=Wellington|isbn=9781776560745|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Fried|first=Albert|year=2001|title=FDR and His Enemies: A History|publisher=St. Martin's Press|isbn=9781250106599|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Gamble|first=Andrew|year=2012|chapter=Debt and Deficits: The Quest for Economic Competence|editor1-last=Cramme|editor1-first=Olaf|editor2-last=Diamond|editor2-first=Patrick|editor2-link=Patrick Diamond|title=After the Third Way: The Future of Social Democracy in Europe|location=London|publisher=I. B. Tauris|pages=45\u201359|isbn=9781848859920|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Giddens|first=Anthony|year=1998|title=The Third Way: The Renewal of Social Democracy|location=Cambridge, England|publi