ing Economic Systems in the Twenty-First Century|edition=7th|publisher=Cengage Learning|isbn=9780618261819|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Hain|first=Peter|year=1995|title=Ayes to the Left|publisher=Lawrence and Wishart|isbn=9780853158325|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Hain|first=Peter|year=2015|title=Back to the Future of Socialism|publisher=Policy Press|page=3|isbn=9781447321682|quote=Crosland's response to 1951 was to develop his 'revisionist' theory of socialism, what today we call democratic socialism or 'social democracy'. By freeing Labour from past fixations that social change had rendered redundant, and by offering fresh objectives to replace those which had already been achieved or whose relevance had faded over time, Crosland showed how socialism made sense in modern society.|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Hamilton|first=Malcolm|year=1989|title=Democratic Socialism in Britain and Sweden|publisher=St Martin's Press|isbn=9781349092345|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Hamby|first=Alonzo L.|year=1999|chapter=Progressivism: A Century of Change and Rebirth|editor-last1=Mileu|editor-first1=Jerome M.|editor-last2=Milkis|editor-first2=Sidney M.|title=Progressivism and the New Democracy|publisher=University of Massachusetts Press|isbn=9781558491922|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Harrington|first=Michael|year=2011|orig-year=1989|title=Socialism: Past and Future|location=New York|publisher=Arcade Publishing|isbn=9781611453355|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Hart|first=John M.|year=1986|chapter=Agrarian Reform|editor1-last=Raat|editor1-first=W. Dirk|editor2-last=Beezley|editor2-first=William H.|title=Twentieth-Century Mexico|location=Lincoln, Nebraska|publisher=University of Nebraska Press|pages=6\u201316|isbn=9780803289147|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Hattersley|first=Roy|year=1987|title=Choose Freedom: The Future of Democratic Socialism|location=Harmondsworth, England|publisher=Penguin|isbn=9780140104943|ref=harv}}\n: {{cite book|last=Hayek|first=Friedrich|year=1944|t